('Asia', 'India', 'Himachal Pradesh', 'Shimla/ Kullu/ Manali', 'Shimla/ Kullu/ Manali', 'Himachal Pradesh is a northern Indian state in the Himalayas. It\'s home to scenic mountain towns and resorts such as Dalhousie. Host to the Dalai Lama, Himachal Pradesh has a strong Tibetan presence. This is reflected in its Buddhist temples and monasteries, as well as its vibrant Tibetan New Year celebrations. The region is also well known for its trekking, climbing and skiing areas.\r\nCapital: Shimla\r\nChief minister: Jai Ram Thakur\r\nPlan a trip\r\nHimachal Pradesh travel guide\r\n13 h 5 min flight\r\nPoints of interest: Rohtang Pass, Solang Valley, Spiti Valley, MORE\r\nChief minister: Jai Ram Thakur\r\nDid you know: Himachal Pradesh has the fifth-highest life expectancy at birth (71.6) during 2010-14 among all Indian states. wikipedia.org', '46055'),
('Asia', 'India', 'Himachal Pradesh', 'HIMACHAL', 'Mystic Kullu/ Manali', 'Himachal Pradesh is a northern Indian state in the Himalayas. It\'s home to scenic mountain towns and resorts such as Dalhousie. Host to the Dalai Lama, Himachal Pradesh has a strong Tibetan presence. This is reflected in its Buddhist temples and monasteries, as well as its vibrant Tibetan New Year celebrations. The region is also well known for its trekking, climbing and skiing areas.\r\nCapital: Shimla\r\nChief minister: Jai Ram Thakur\r\nPlan a trip\r\nHimachal Pradesh travel guide\r\n13 h 5 min flight\r\nPoints of interest: Rohtang Pass, Solang Valley, Spiti Valley, MORE\r\nChief minister: Jai Ram Thakur\r\nDid you know: Himachal Pradesh has the fifth-highest life expectancy at birth (71.6) during 2010-14 among all Indian ', '56167'),
