('Asia', 'Singapore', 'Andhra Pradesh', 'SINGAPORE', 'SINGAPORE', 'Singapore, an island city-state off southern Malaysia, is a global financial center with a tropical climate and multicultural population. Its colonial core centers on the Padang, a cricket field since the 1830s and now flanked by grand buildings such as City Hall, with its 18 Corinthian columns. In Singapore\'s circa-1820 Chinatown stands the red-and-gold Buddha Tooth Relic Temple, said to house one of Buddha\'s teeth.\r\nDialing code: +65\r\nCurrency: Singapore dollar\r\nPopulation: 56.1 lakhs', '14911'),
('Asia', 'Malaysia', 'Other', 'MALAYSIA', 'MALAYSIA', 'Malaysia is a Southeast Asian country occupying parts of the Malay Peninsula and the island of Borneo. It\'s known for its beaches, rainforests and mix of Malay, Chinese, Indian and European cultural influences. The capital, Kuala Lumpur, is home to colonial buildings, busy shopping districts such as Bukit Bintang and skyscrapers such as the iconic, 451m-tall Petronas Twin Towers.\r\nPrime minister: Mahathir Bin Mohamad Trending\r\nCapital: Kuala Lumpur\r\nDialing code: +60\r\nCurrency: Malaysian ringgit\r\nPlan a trip', '26299'),
