('Asia', 'Indonesia', 'Other', 'KUTA-KINTAMANI -BENOA BEACH ', 'BALI ', 'Bali is an Indonesian island known for its forested volcanic mountains, iconic rice paddies, beaches and coral reefs. The island is home to religious sites such as cliffside Uluwatu Temple. To the south, the beachside city of Kuta has lively bars, while Seminyak, Sanur and Nusa Dua are popular resort towns. The island is also known for its yoga and meditation retreats.\r\nArea: 5,780 kmÂ²\r\nCapital: Denpasar\r\nPopulation: 42.3 lakhs (2014)', '12287'),
