(0, '849117', 'Char Dham Yatra ', 'Summer', NULL, '54790', 'Domestic', '11', '10', 'Char Dham Yatra ', '27500', '00', 'Group,Family Only,Weekend,', 'Shri Kedarnath Badrinath Gangotri & Yamunotri', 'India', 'Hotel,Bus,Dinner,Transfer SIC,Sightseeing,', '4 Star,', '', '484049,', 'lifetime', 'Active', '1556095724.jpg', 'The Char Dham is a set of four pilgrimage sites in India. Vaishnavite Hindus believe that visiting these sites helps achieve \"Moksha\". It comprises Badrinath, Dwaraka, Puri and Rameswaram. It is considered by Hindus that every Hindu must visit the char dhams ', '2019-04-24 08:48:43', 'NA'),
(0, '444285', 'Chardham Yatra WITH  Helicopter  ', 'Weekend', NULL, '97980', 'Domestic', '5', '4', 'Chardham Yatra WITH  Helicopter  ', '178000', '00', 'Couple Only,Bachelor,', 'Dehradun', 'India', 'Air,Hotel,Lunch,Dinner,Transfer SIC,Guide,Sightseeing,', '4 Star,', 'Others', '484049,', 'lifetime', 'Active', '1556108975.jpg', '\r\nYatra  starts  from   the  capital  of  Uttarakhand,  the  queen  of  the  hills, Dehradun.  These  four  different  pilgrim  destinations,  the  Char  Dhams, situated  in  the  magical Himalayas, joined   by  mysticism  and   spirituality, beckon  millions of visitors every  year for  a  voyage  into  the unknown, for  a\r\nflight towards the heavens, for a journey into  the self\r\n', '2019-04-24 12:29:35', 'NA'),
(0, '657038', 'AMAZING  THAILAND ', 'Weekend', NULL, '80207', 'International', '6', '5', 'AMAZING  THAILAND ', '55000', '00', 'Group,Family Only,Friends,Weekend,,,', 'BANGKOK', 'Thailand', 'Air,Hotel,Lunch,Dinner,Transfer PVT,Criuse,Sightseeing,,,', '3 Star,,,', 'Others', '484049,', 'lifetime', 'Active', '1557390794.jpg', 'Thailand is a Southeast Asian country. It\'s known for tropical beaches, opulent royal palaces, ancient ruins and ornate temples displaying figures of Buddha. In Bangkok, the capital, an ultramodern cityscape rises next to quiet canalside communities and the iconic temples of Wat Arun, Wat Pho and the Emerald Buddha Temple (Wat Phra Kaew). Nearby beach resorts include bustling Pattaya and fashionable Hua Hin.\r\nKing: Maha Vajiralongkorn Trending\r\nCapital: Bangkok\r\nDialing code: +66\r\nCurrency: Thai baht\r\nPoints of interest: The Grand Palace, Phi Phi Islands, Pa Tong  ', '2019-04-28 07:17:15', 'NA'),
(0, '280477', 'Thailand Super Saver - 2019', 'Weekend', NULL, '53544', 'International', '6', '5', 'Thailand Super Saver - 2019', '52000', '00', 'Couple Only,Family Only,Friends,Weekend,,,,,', 'BANGKOK', 'Thailand', 'Air,Hotel,Lunch,Dinner,Transfer PVT,Criuse,Sightseeing,,,,,', '3 Star,', 'Others', '484049,', 'lifetime', 'Active', '1557390000.jpg', 'Thailand is one the most popular countries in Asia and is famous for its delightful culture, stunning sandy beaches, Thai culinary delicacies and some wonderful tourist attractions. Tourists can experience the euphoria of Thailand in Pattaya. \r\n Renowned as one of the worldâ€™s top beach destinations, Pattaya has been luring adventure-seekers for decades with an intoxicating mix of eateries and shops, luxury resorts, wild parties and high-octane water sports. Pattaya is located on the east coast of the Gulf of Thailand, just 150 kilometers from the capital â€“ Bangkok.\r\n The beach city draws in hordes of tourists and expats from all over the world. You can choose to get lost in the natural beauty or get taken over by the allure of the cabaret stage. This region is famous for its varied nightlife, which gave it the name â€˜the naughty sister of Bangkok.\' However, now there are a lot more attractions and activities for everyone. There are botanical gardens, golf courses, water sports, and museums. Other places of interest include the Pattaya Floating Market, Nong Nooch Village, Sanctuary of Truth, Mini Siam, Underwater World Pattaya and more.    ', '2019-04-29 08:09:54', 'NA'),
