('954641', 6, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.Shimla- Kufri- sightseeing\r\nMEALS: Breakfast and dinner only \r\nAfter breakfast proceed for Kufri sightseeing \"Kufri\" India\'s One Of The Best Holiday Paradise famous for its Himalayan park, pony and yak ride one can see wide endless Himalayan panorama from kufri, also take a romantic view of Thick Deodar and pine forest, back to Shimla, transfer to lift, visit The Mall road, The Ridge, the world famous international Gaiety theater and shopping for family, friends and loved one, back to hotel, dinner and rest overnight at hotel.\r\n', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
('954641', 7, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.Shimla-Delhi (370 Kms 8-9 hrs)\r\nMEALS: Breakfast only \r\nAfter breakfast check out hotel it\'s time to say Good Bye to Queen of Hill Station\'s Shimla with life time memories, proceed to Delhi by luxury Volvo Bus [at 08.00 PM OR 8:00 AM] (Sightseeing in Shimla will be provided at additional cost.) on last day. Next Morning arrival at Delhi at 06:00 am.\r\n', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
('175260', 1, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.Pathankot â€“ Dharamshala (110 kms/3-4 hrs)\r\nMEALS: Dinner only On arrival at Pathankot Railway Station you \r\nwill met or assisted by our representative and drive for Dharamshala,\r\n Enroute cover Chamunda Devi Temple & Kangra Temple. On arrival \r\ncheck in to the hotel, Dinner and overnight stay in the hotel.\r\n', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
('175260', 2, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.Dharamshala â€“ Local Sightseeing\r\nMEALS: Breakfast & Dinner only\r\nAfter breakfast sightseeing and excursion to Dharamshala and places nearby. Today cover MecloedGanj, Dalai Lama Residence, Dal Lake, Bhagsu Nath Temple, Waterfall & Markets. Dinner and rest overnight at hotel.\r\nDharamshala is a hill-station lying on the spur of the Dhauladhar Mountains about 18 kms north-east of Kangra, in the State of Himachal Pradesh and overlooks a wide spread of plains. It is known for its scenic beauty set amidst high pine and oak trees. Dharamshalaâ€™s altitude varies between 4400 ft. and 6560 ft. Since 1960, when it became the temporary headquarters of His Holiness the Dalai Lama, Dharamshala has risen to international repute as â€œThe Little Lhasa in Indiaâ€. Covering a wide area in the form of a twin settlement, Lower Dharamshala (1380 m) is a busy commercial center, while Upper Dharamshala (1830 m) with the suburbs of McLeod Ganj and Forsythganj retain a British flavor and colonial lifestyle. There is also a large Tibetan community in exile, who has made this their home, living mostly in McLeod Ganj.\r\n', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
('175260', 3, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.Dharamshala - Dalhousie (140 kms/3-4 hrs)\r\nMEALS: Breakfast and Dinner only\r\nAfter breakfast check out hotel and depart for Dalhousie on arrival\r\n check in hotel after fresh up visit Panjpulla a memorial is built in\r\n memory of Sardar Ajit Singh, one of the Indian\'s well-loved freedom \r\nfighter and uncle of Sardar Bhagat singh. Panjpulla has a small lake with \r\nboating facility and is the nearest picnic spot. At Panjpulla, a waterfall is also there. Dinner and overnight stay at hotel\r\n', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
('175260', 4, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.Dalhousie - Khajjiar - Dalhousie\r\nMEALS: Breakfast and Dinner only\r\nAfter Breakfast drive towards Khajjiar. Excursion to Khajjiar 24 kms from Dalhousie surrounded by thick Deodar forest. Enroute cover Kala Top Sanctuary. Drive from Dalhousie to Khajjiar is awesome, Full day at Khajjiar enjoy natural beauty of Khajjiar. Khajjiar is also called Mini Switzerland. Come back to Dalhousie hotel. Dinner and rest overnight at Hotel.\r\n\r\n\r\n', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
('175260', 5, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.Dalhousie- Pathankot (90 kms/2-3 hrs)\r\nMEALS: Breakfast only\r\nAfter breakfast check out from hotel and drive towards Pathankot. Drop at Pathankot Railway station for your further journey.\r\n', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
('372276', 1, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.Leh â€“ Arrival\r\nOn arrival, our representative(s) arrange for the transfer\r\n to your hotel. Check into the hotel and use the rest of \r\nthe day to rest and get acclimatized to the high altitude\r\n (3500 meters/11800 ft) and low air pressure in Leh. \r\nStrolling around the local markets maybe a good idea during\r\n the evening. Overnight stay is arranged at the Hotel. \r\n', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
('372276', 2, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.Leh â€“ Local Sightseeing\r\nPost Breakfast we proceed for Indus Valley Monastery tour including Shey, The ancient capital of Ladakh, Thiksey an impressive complex rising tier upon tier on a hill above the village, Stok Palace & Sindhu Ghat. Evening come back to hotel. Overnight at Hotel.\r\n', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
('372276', 3, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.Leh â€“ Khardongla Pass â€“ Leh\r\nmorning starts with a visit to Khardongla Pass which, at 18360 ft,  is the world\'s highest motorable pass. During the afternoon, you are introduced to a local family in Stok village which serves delicious home made butter tea and barley drink. Later, visit the Thiksey Monastery which houses the most photographed statue of Maitreya Buddha in India.  Return by evening for overnight stay at the hotel.\r\n', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
('372276', 4, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.Leh â€“ Pangong Lake â€“ Leh\r\nIn the early morning of the penultimate day, an excursion is scheduled to Pangong Lake, a 135 km drive from Leh. The Pangong Lake is 140km long and 3-5km in width â€“ more than half of which lies in Tibetan territory. As you return back Leh by evening, you can use the remaining time exploring local markets, looking for a decent bargain. Overnight stay is again at the hotel. \r\n', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
('372276', 5, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.:  Leh â€“ Drop\r\nEarly morning transfer to KBR airport to board flight for onward journey.\r\n', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
('465371', 1, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.:  Srinagar â€“ Arrival\r\nOn arrival at Srinagar Airport/Railway station meet or\r\n greet by our representative & drive towards Srinagar hotel. \r\nCheck into the hotel & overnight stay.\r\n', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
('465371', 2, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.Srinagar â€“ Kargil (205 Kms 7-8 Hrs)\r\nMorning check out from hotel & depart for Kargil which is about 205 kilometers from Srinagar. En-route, stop at the valley of meadows Sonmarg for lunch and then crossover the Zojila pass which is located 3900 meter above the sea level. After driving for some time, reach the Drass Village which is said to be the 2nd coldest place on earth after Siberia in Russia. By the evening, you will reach Kargil town; upon reaching there, check in at hotel/deluxe camp for overnight stay.\r\n', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
('465371', 3, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.Kargil â€“ Leh (213 Kms 7-8 Hrs)\r\nPost breakfast embark on a drive to Leh which is 230 kilometers from Kargil town. En-route visit the ancient rock cut statue of Maitreya Buddha at Mulbekh village. Later stop for photo at lunar like landscapes near Lamayuru Monastery. On the way, enjoy a mouth tempting lunch and photo stop at the sangam of Indus and Zanskar rivers. By the evening, arrive Leh and check in at the hotel in Leh.\r\n', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
('465371', 4, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.Leh â€“ Local Sightseeing\r\nPost Breakfast we proceed for Indus Valley Monastery tou\r\nr including Shey, The ancient capital of Ladakh, Thiksey an impressive \r\ncomplex rising tier upon tier on a hill above the village, Stok Palace & \r\nSindhu Ghat. Evening come back to hotel. Overnight at Hotel.\r\n', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
('465371', 5, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.:  Leh â€“ Khardungla Pass 18,390Ft. â€“ Nubra Valley\r\nPost breakfast we drive to Khardongla, over Khardung La (One of The Highest Motorable Road In The World) at 5,602 Mtrs /18,390 Ft, around 39 km from Leh. From the pass, one can see all the way south over the Indus valley to seemingly endless peaks and ridges of the Zanskar range,and north to the giants of the Saser massif. Upon arrival in Khardong la group will spend some time over there & then drive to nubra Valley, enroute visit Deskit monastery, Evening arrive at Nubra Valley. Visit Hundar & Sand dunes. you can take ride of double humped camel there. Check into the hotel/camp & overnight stay.\r\n', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
('465371', 6, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.Valley â€“ Khardongla Top â€“ 18,390 Ft â€“ Leh\r\nPost breakfast we shall drive back to Leh, Check into the hotel & overnight stay.\r\n', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
('465371', 7, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.Leh â€“ Pangong Lake â€“ Leh\r\nIn the early morning of the penultimate day, an excursion is scheduled to Pangong Lake, a 135 km drive from Leh. The Pangong Lake is 140km long and 3-5km in width â€“ more than half of which lies in Tibetan territory. As you return back Leh by evening, you can use the remaining time exploring local markets, looking for a decent bargain. Overnight stay is again at the hotel. \r\n', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
('465371', 8, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.Leh â€“ Kargil (213 Kms 7-8 Hrs)\r\nMorning check out from hotel & drive towards Kargil which is 230 kilometers from Leh town. Enroute you can cover Magnetic Hill, Pathar Sahib Gurudwara & Confluence of Indus & Zanskar river. By the evening, arrive Kargil and check in at the hotel in Kargil.\r\n\r\nDay 9:  Kargil â€“ Srinagar (205 Kms 7-8 Hrs)\r\nMorning check out from hotel & depart for Srinagar. Evening arrive at Srinagar. Drop at Srinagar Airport for your further journey.\r\n', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
('984309', 1, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.Arrival at Port Blair to to Corbynâ€™s and Sound and Light Show at Cellular Jail\r\nOn arrive at Port Blair, our representative receive you at Airport and escorted you to check in to the Hotel / Resort. After check-in at the hotel In the afternoon proceed for visit to Corbynâ€™s cove beach â€“ a coconut fringed beach about 8kms from Port Blair city ideal for swimming, visit to National Memorial Cellular Jail- was built by Britishers in the years 1905 to imprison Indian political freedom fighters, Late evening witness the enthralling Sound and Light Show at Cellular Jail - where the heroic saga of the Indian freedom struggle is brought alive. Overnight stay at respective Hotel / Resort at Port Blair.\r\n', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
('984309', 2, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.Port Blair to Ross Island and Excursion to Coral island North Bay\r\nAfter breakfast, start, Visit Ross Island, the former residential and \r\nadministrative island of the British during their rule of South East \r\nAsia, was nick named the Paris of the East. This island was \r\ncompletely destroyed in an earthquake, now in ruins. and \r\nexcursion to Coral Island (North Bay) to see coral reefs, \r\nexotic varieties of beautiful ornamental fish and other marine \r\nlife. This is an ideal place for snorkelling as this sandy beach \r\ncoupled with clear water creates a breath-taking spectacle. \r\nPlease carry your lunch pack, drinking water & changing dress.( water sports activities available here are Scuba diving , Under water sea-walk , Snorkelling , glass bottom boat ride Jet ski- water scooter , Banana boat ride , speed boat etc. on direct payment basis) Overnight stay at respective Hotel at Port Blair.\r\n\r\n', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
('984309', 3, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.Port Blair to Neil Island.\r\nIn the morning at Phoenix Bay Harbor to transfer to Neil Island via \r\nferry from Port Blair. On arrival at Neil Island, our representative will \r\nreceive and escort you to check-in to the resort. After relaxation trip to\r\n Neil Sightseen, laxmanpur, Sitapur, Bharatpur and Howra Bridge .\r\nOvernight stay at Neil Island.\r\n', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
('984309', 4, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.Neil Island to Havelock Island\r\nToday, we start our journey towards Havelock island via ferry from Neil Island Harbour. On arrival at Havelock Island, our representative will receive and escort you to Radhanagar Beach (Beach No. 7), the Times Magazine rated the finest beach among the best beaches in Asia. It is an ideal place for swimming, sea bathing and basking on the sun kissed beach. . On arrival proceed to selected hotel. Stay here overnight amongst sandy beach and lush green forest in a comfortable beach resort.Havelock.\r\n', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
('984309', 5, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.Havelock  to Port Blair to Chidiyatapu With Sun Set Point.\r\nAccording  Boat  Schedule   you reach back  Portblair  by ferry. On arrive at Port Blair, our representative receive you at  Phonix Bay harbour and escorted you to check in to the Hotel / Resort. to  visit Chidiya Tapu is the southern most tip of South Andaman. As its name this is favorite destination for bird watchers. Its lush green mangroves, forest cover with numerous chirping birds and the Sylvan Sands make it an ideal picnic site. A very beautiful beach named Munda Pahad near by is very famous amongst the local people. There is a forest guesthouse situated on top of a hillock providing a fabulous view of isolated islands, breath-taking sunset also called the sunset point,then back to Hotel. . Overnight stay at P/B.\r\n', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
('984309', 6, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.Port Blair to Bratang Island sightseen, lime stone cave\r\nEarly morning departure (110Kms) which holds the nature\'s best \r\ntreasures gifted to the Islands. Limestone caves are a must see \r\npoints for nature lovers & leisure travelers alike. The Road \r\njourney from Portblair to Baratang involves crossing through \r\ncreeks and dense equatorial forest. In the evening proceed for \r\nPort Blair. Overnight stay at P/B.\r\n', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
('984309', 7, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.Port Blair â€“ City tour\r\nAfter breakfast, start for a day \"City Tour\" of Port Blair - covering Cellular Jail- Better known as Kalapani â€“was built by Britishers in the year 1905 to imprison Indian freedom fighter, Chatham Saw Mill (one of the oldest & largest in Asia), Forest Museum, Anthropological museum, Navel museum, -, Fisheries (Marine) Museum is, cottage industries free for shopping activities. Overnight stay at respective Hotel / Resort at Port Blair.\r\n', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
('984309', 8, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.From PortBlair\r\nTransfer to Airport and Departure with a wonderful holiday memories\r\n', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
('512306', 1, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.Pick up from Airport, Carbynâ€™s Cove Beach, Cellular jail and Sound and Light show\r\nOur representative will receive you at Veer Savarkar Airport, Port Blair and will escort to the hotel, he will also assist you to do hotel check-in formalities. After check-in and little relax,\r\n you will be taken to the following places.Corbynsâ€™ Cove Beach: The \r\nCorbynsâ€™ Cove, is a serene and unspoiled soft sandy beach, set in \r\npicturesque background of lush green coconut palms and pleasant blue\r\n sea. The main attractions of this beach are the inviting water sports. The \r\nCorbynsâ€™ Cove beach, situated 8 kms from the City centre is the closest\r\n Beach from the city. This coconut- palm fringed beach, is ideal for \r\nswimming and sun bathing.Cellular Jail: This historic building was built in\r\n the 19th century to look like a wheel with seven spokes. Today only three wings of the seven remain. It took 10 years to complete. It is called â€˜Cellularâ€™ because it is â€œCells beyond Cellsâ€.Sound & Light Show: At the National Memorial â€˜Cellular Jailâ€™ you can attend the Sound & Light Show where the heroic saga of the Indian Freedom Struggle is brought alive by the means of light and sound at the jail premises, presented in English and Hindi, which takes you back to the British Era.\r\nNight Stay at Port Blair.\r\n', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
('512306', 2, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.Onward journey to Havelock (57kms) & Radhanagar beach\r\nIn the morning you will be escorted to Phoenix Bay Harbor to board luxury ferry  which will take you to Havelock Island.Havelock Island: The Island is named after a British Army Officer.\r\n The island offers state-of-the-art facilities for snorkeling and scuba \r\ndiving. Havelock is famous for its white sand and crystal clear and \r\ntransparent waters.At the Harbour our representative will receive \r\nyou and will escort you to the Hotel for checkin process. After \r\ncheckin proceed to Radhanagar Beach, the best and famous beach \r\nof Andaman Islands. You can go for swimming or can enjoy the beautiful place.\r\nNight Stay at Havelock Island. \r\n\r\n', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
('512306', 3, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.:  Depart from Havelock and onward journey to Neil Island.\r\nCheck out from the hotel, move towards the Harbor to board a ferry which will take you to Neil Island. At the harbor our representative will receive you and will escort you to the hotel/resort.\r\nNeil Island:This Island is apparently named after James George Smith Neill, a British soldier responsible for several war crimes during the suppression of the 1857 Mutiny. There is a lone jetty at Bharathpur, which serves as the only entryâ€“exit point of the island.   Night Stay at Neil Island\r\n', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
('512306', 4, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.Neil Island tour and return to Port Blair\r\nOur representative will escort you to the siteseeing tour of Neil Island, which will include Bharatpur Beach & Laxshmanpur Beach and Natural Bridge like structure called Hawda \r\nBridge by locals. In the evening we will start our return journey to \r\nPort Blair enjoying the sea breeze and the sight of the changing colors \r\nof the sky of the setting sun and most of the time accompanied by \r\ndolphins and flying fishes swimming along the boat.\r\nNight Stay at Port Blair. \r\n\r\n', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
('512306', 5, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.Baratang Island\r\nEarly morning before daybreak we depart for Baratang Islands. It is approximately 110 kms away from Port Blair. It is connected through road passing through Jarawas Tribe Reserve also known as ATR Road (Andaman Trunk Road or the State High Way).  We will travel through fabulous and enchanting forest in conveys to reach Nilambur Jetty (Middle Strait) from where we take a ferry for Baratang Island which is a 15mints ride. It has thick mangrove creeks on both sides followed by dense tropical forest. Major attractions at Baratang are lime Stone Cave and Mud Volcanoes.\r\nLime Stone Cave: They are located 15 mints away by sea from Baratang Jetty. We can reach there by dongis or small boats. The journey enthralls everyone as it takes you underneath the dense forest of mangroves plantation. Please do carry sufficient water along with you.\r\nMud Volcano (Jalki): The mud volcanoes have erupted so sporadically with recent eruption I n 2005, believed to have been associated with the 2004 earthquake. The natives of this island call it â€œJalkiâ€. The mud volcanoes squirt little fountains of mud.  Night Stay at Port Blair. \r\n', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
('512306', 6, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.Departure from Port Blair\r\nCheck out and pick up from the hotel and transfer to Port Blair Airport \r\n/ Harbour for your onward journey back home, carrying wonderful memoriesâ€¦\r\nOnly Bsnl, Airtel and Vodafone mobile network works in Andaman\r\n', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
('537893', 1, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.ARRIVAL AND TRANSFER TO GANGTOK\r\n Our representative will be there to receive the Guest at New Jalpaiguri Railway Station (NJP) / Bagdogra Airport (IXB) / Tenzing Norgay Bus Stand (Junction) â€“ He will be assisting for the transfer to Gangtok â€“ Gangtok the capital of Sikkim Suits all from tranquility to adventure, land of monastery, mystic rituals & festivals at an height of 1670 meters / 5480 feet and is the most visited spot of India. It is one of the most beautiful town with varieties of Rhododendron, Orchids and butterflies - Nearly 135 kilometers 4 Â½ - 5 hours drive â€“ Check into hotel â€“ Evening free to roam around M G Road (Mall) or local Shopping center - Over Night stay at Gangtok.\r\n', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
('537893', 2, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.EXCURSION TO TSOMGO LAKE & BABA MANDIR(FULL DAY)\r\n Morning breakfast at hotel â€“ Excursion to Tsomgo Lake & Baba Mandir ( New ) nearly 40 kilometers - The Lake is oval shaped lake nearly 50 feet deep - Generally covered in snow for most of the year the year â€“ This lake is home to the Brahmini ducks & many migratory birds â€“ Nearby is the sacred Baba Mandir known to be a very holy site for all - Nathu La Pass to Republic of China is nearly 20 kilometers and is optional tour - Back to Gangtok - Evening free to roam around M G Road (Mall) or local Shopping center - Over Night stay at Gangtok (Incase of Landslide or due to any other reasons ifTshangu Lake is closed then an alternate sightseeing will be provided).\r\n', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
('537893', 3, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.GANGTOK LOCAL SIGHT SEEING (HALF DAY) & TRANSFER TO KALIMPONG\r\n Morning breakfast - After breakfast drive for the city tour of Gangtok â€“ Visit to Directorate of Handicrafts & Handloom, Research Institute of Tibetology, Do Drul Chorten (Stupa), Enchey Monastery,White Hall, Flower Showâ€“ Transfer to Kalimpong - 105 kilometers 2 - 2 Â½ hours - Kalimpong situated on the foothills of the Himalayas is a green destination at an altitude of 1243 meters / 4078 feet - It is a historical destinations with bustling market, colorful people â€“ Check into hotel â€“ Evening free to roam around the any of the nurseries or the Local market area - Overnight stay at Kalimpong.\r\n\r\n', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
('537893', 4, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.KALIMPONG SIGHT SEEING & TRANSFER TO DARJEELING\r\n Morning breakfast - Drive for sight seeing tour through scenic road to Forest Museum (Closed On Thursday), Deolo Hill, Hanuman Mandir, Dr Graham Homes, Durbin Monastery, Mangaldham, Pine View Nurseries (Cactus Only) â€“ Transfer to Darjeeling crossing the river Teesta on the way - 65 kilometers 1 Â½ - 2 hours - At an height of 2123 meters / 70001 feet lies the land of breathtaking beauty, sloping tea gardens with spectacular views of the Mount Everest is the Queen of the hills â€“ It is also home to the famous World Heritage train â€“ The Darjeeling Himalayan Railway (DHR) - Check into hotel â€“ Evening free to roam around Mall or local Shopping center - Over Night stay at Darjeeling.\r\n', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
('537893', 5, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.DARJEELING LOCAL SIGHT SEEING (HALF DAY)\r\n Early morning at around3:45 AM drive to 8000 feet / 2440 meters through primitive forests of oak, magnolia to Tiger Hillto view sunrise over Kanchendzonga Peak (subject to clear weather) â€“ On the way back visit Ghoom Monastery, Peace memorial & Batasia Loop â€“ On the way back visit Ghoom Monastery, Peace memorial & Batasia Loop â€“ Back to hotel for breakfast - After breakfast rest for half an hour After breakfast next round of sight seeing - Half Day city tour includes Padmaja Naidu Zoological Park, Himalayan Mountaineering Institute (Closed on Thursday), Ropeway, Tensing Gumpo Rock, Tibetan Refugee Self Help Center (Closed on Sunday), Tea Estate, Natural History Museum (Sunday Closed), Peace Pagoda â€“ Back to hotel â€“ Evening free to stroll around the area - Overnight stay at Darjeeling.\r\n', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
('537893', 6, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.DEPARTURE â€“ DARJEELING TO SILIGURI / NEW JALPAIGURI RAILWAY STATION (NJP) / BAGDOGRA AIRPORT (IXB) / TENZING NORGAY BUS STAND (JUNCTION)\r\n Morning breakfast - After breakfast transfer to Siliguri / New Jalpaiguri Railway Station (NJP) / Bagdogra Airport (IXB) / Tenzing Norgay Bus Stand (Junction) - Nearly 105 kilometers 3 Â½ - 4 hours drive â€“ Forwarding Journey.\r\n\r\n', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
('590025', 1, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.ARRIVAL AT BANGALORE\r\n Our representative will receive you on arrival at Bangalore Airport/ Railway station. Transfer and check in to hotel. After check in at Hotel proceeds to enjoy the sightseeing of Tippu Temple, Bull Temple, Lal Bag gardens etc. Overnight at hotel.\r\n', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
('590025', 2, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.BANGALORE TO MYSORE\r\n After breakfast drive to Mysore (142 Kms and 4 Hrs drives). Check in at Hotel. \r\nPrecedes sightseeing. Including: Chammundi Hills and Nandi, Maharaja Palace, \r\nRanganthittu bird sanctuary etc. Rest day free and overnight at hotel.\r\n', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
('590025', 3, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.MYSORE TO OOTY\r\n After breakfast enjoys rest of sightseeing. Later drive to Ooty (142 Kms and 5\r\n Hrs drive). On arrival check in at Hotel. Visit Dodda Betta Peak, which gives a\r\n view of Ooty from the heights of Nilgiri. Later move for seeing Conoor Tea \r\nGardens, Sim\'s Park offering some wonderful views of varieties of flowers & \r\ntrees and Dolphin\'s Nose which offers scenic beauty of small mountains, springs, \r\ntea gardens etc from the top. You can indulge in hiking, boating, trekking, and \r\nhorse riding also. Overnight is in Ooty.\r\n\r\n', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
('590025', 4, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.OOTY After breakfast we take you for a visit to the Botanical Garden. Botanical \r\nGarden in opty is well known and one of the oldest botanical garden in \r\ncountry. It is also special for its green lawns, rare trees, variety of different \r\ncollections of flowering plants, clear watered pools etc. Enjoy the gardens \r\nand then transfer back to the hotel in the evening. Night stay is in Ooty.\r\n', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
('590025', 5, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.OOTY TO KODAIKANAL\r\n After breakfast drive to Kodaikanal (250 Kms and 7 Hrs drives). Kodaikanal is a beautiful hill station with Bracing climate at the height of 2133m. Check in at Hotel. Later visit Kodaikanal lake, silver cascade waterfalls, lambs rock, Dolphin nose, Fairy Falls-, Kurinji Andavar Temple, Shenbaganur Museum, Pillar Rocks Green Valley View etc. Overnight at the hotel.\r\n', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
('590025', 6, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.KODAIKANAL\r\nAfter breakfast take a trek into the Pine forests and enjoy the healthiest air \r\nand beautiful surrounding also leisurely visit the Astrophysical Solar Observatory \r\nand the Orchidarium which has more than 300 species of orchids. Overnight at hotel.\r\n', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
('523590', 1, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.Goa Arrival \r\nOn Arrival in Goa we will meet you at Airport/Station and transfer to Hotel, check in hotel  No Sightseeing   \r\n  ', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
('523590', 2, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.North Goa (10am to 5:30pm)     \r\nAfter Breakfast Visit  Drive to Fort Aguada â€“ Vagator Beach - Anjuna Beach - Baga Beach - Calangute Beach - back to your hotel. ', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
('523590', 3, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '. South Goa Tour (10am to 7:30pm)   \r\nDrive to Old Goa Churches - Mangeshi Temple - Spice Plantation (entry Rs. 400/head including lunch to be paid extra direct) - Dona Paula Jetty - Panjim City Market Shopping â€“ 1hr Boat Cruise (entry Rs. 300/head to be paid extra direct) - back to your hotel.', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
