('675958', 5, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.ZURICH\r\nBreakfast at the hotel. Later, proceed for your city tour of Zurich.You\'ll see all the main attractions of this busy cultural and commercial centre, including the mediaeval Old Town and elegant Bahnhofstrasse before climbing to the Zurichberg by funicular railway for some great views over the city. Just sit back in a comfortable coach as your knowledgeable guide points out all the top sights, telling you all about this beautiful city. \r\n\r\nWe\'ll pass by the Swiss National Museum, built in the style of a French Chateau, the shopping and business quarter centred onthe exclusive Bahnhofstrasse, the Limmatquai quarter and the medieval Old Town with views up to the Lindenhof, where the brave women of Zurich saved the city from invaders. You\'ll also admire the largest church clock-face in Europe at the Church of St. Peter, the patriarchal Guild Houses, and the Opera house. We\'ll make a brief photo stop by the picturesque Lake Zurich, before boarding the funicular railway for the climb up to the Zurichberg district with its recently renovated five-star Grand Hotel Dolder and many superb 19th Century mansions. Other highlights of the tour are the University and the Swiss Federal Institute of Technology, where Albert Einstein was both student and professor. Finally we\'ll stop at the Fraumunster Church where you can admire the magnificent windows decorated by Marc Chagal. Rest of the day at leisure. Overnight at yourhotel.\r\n', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
('675958', 6, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.ZURICH- LUCERNE (by train)\r\nBreakfast at the hotel. Check out and make your way to the station for your onward journey to Lucerne. On arrival at Lucerne station, make your own way to your hotel. Check in. Rest of the day at leisure. You can explore on foot the city highlights including the Chapel Bridge, the Old Town, Lake Lucerne, various Museums and many more attractions. Overnight at your hotel.\r\n\r\n', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
