('178661', 1, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.Upon your arrival in Bangkok, Transfers to Pattaya, which is a short 2 hours drive from Bangkok. Check in to the hotel .Time to relax!!\r\n\r\nIn the evening, we recommend that you take an optional tour of Alcazar Show(at additional cost). The Alcazar Show a world-famous cabaret, which can give the Lido and Moulin Rouge of Paris, a run for their money, featuring a grand theatre with 1200 seats and thousands of watts of pulsating sound.\r\n\r\nOvernight at Hotel in Pattaya.\r\n\r\n*Hotel Standard Check in time is 2PM -4PM. To avail guaranteed early check in please pay INR 1,200 per person at the time of booking. Also, hotel guaranteed check-in is subject to availability at the time of booking.', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
('178661', 2, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.Coral island with Lunch\r\nAfter breakfast, After Breakfast,  for Coral Island Tour\r\n\r\nIf you take this tour, you will be transferred to the sparkling blue waters of the Gulf of Thailand by a speedboat, and arrive at the idyllic Coral Island (Koh Lan), where you will spend the day luxuriating under the welcoming tropical sun. You can lounge, swim, snorkel or simply enjoy the sun at the islandâ€™s immaculate golden beaches. You all have the option of viewing the beautiful coral formations around the island either through a glass-bottom boat or by diving in. Upon your return from the island, you will enjoy a scrumptious Indian lunch at Pattaya. Coral Island tour on join/shared speed boat will stop for Parasailing for those who are interested. Those who are not interested in Parasailing will wait for the rest to finish the activity.\r\nEvening is free at leisure. Overnight in Pattaya.\r\nTravel tip: Donâ€™t forget to carry your swimsuit, sunscreen and towel.', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
('178661', 3, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.Pattya  hotel after Breakfast proceed to Bangkok hotel traf pvt \r\n\r\n\r\nBangkok City & Temples Tour by Tour East\r\nStopping over in Bangkok and looking for a taste of what the \r\ncity has to offer? Book this tour of Bangkok\'s best sightseeing \r\nspots and temples and get your fix of the cultural immersion \r\nthat the city has to offer. Your tour starts at Wat Traimit, \r\nthe temple which is famous for holding the largest golden \r\nBuddha in the world, standing at five meters in height and \r\nover five and half tonnes. Then you\'ll pass through the city\'s \r\nChinatown to glimpse the cultural diversity in the city center,\r\n before heading to Wat Pho, an ancient Buddhist temple \r\ncomplex, which holds more Buddha statues than any other \r\ntemple in the country. Your last stop is at the Marble Temple, \r\nor Wat Benchamabopit, the most beautiful of Bangkok\'s temples, \r\nand made of imported Italian marble. This is a wonderful tour of \r\nBangkok\'s cultural richness and diversity and one that no traveler should miss.\r\nMeals:, Lunch & Dinner.\r\nThere is no service included, you may spend time, as per your interests.\r\n', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
