('753978', 2, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.Vienna\r\nBreakfast at hotel. Then proceed for Vienna City Tour using you Vienna Hop on hop off ticket. Rest of the day at leisure. Overnight at your hotel.\r\n\r\nGet the chance to know more about Vienna on a deeper level as you absorb the fascinating history. Youâ€™ll be able to see where the events went on as you seemingly float from one historic spot to the other. Our informative and intriguing audio guide adds a special touch to the experience.\r\nWitness a choice of breath-taking architecture, admire the cityâ€™s marvelous castles, gardens, monuments and also its pristine parks. The Austrian capital encompasses almost everything from the many traditions from within the country to the Roman, Gothic and Baroque constructions.\r\n\r\n', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
('753978', 3, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.Vienna â€“ Salzburg\r\nBreakfast at your hotel, check out. Make your own way to the train station for your onward journey to Salzburg. On arrival at Salzburg station, make your own way to your hotel. Check in. Rest for few hours and then proceed for your Salzburg city tour.Rest of the day at leisure. Overnight at your hotel.\r\nSee the best sight and attractions in Salzburg with this whistle-stop, one-hour express tour by bus. Discover the cityâ€™s astonishing musical legacy; admire its awe-inspiring architecture and its rich culture heritage while learning all about its fascinating history and the people whose talent and inspiration helped make it one of Europeâ€™s most beautiful cities. Marvel at the Mirabel palace and its beautifully landscaped gardens, which together are a UNESCO world heritage site. Pass the internationally renowned Mozarteum music university and the magnificent marionette theatre, which for a century has been producing marionette performances of Mozartâ€™s operas. ', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
('753978', 4, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.Salzburg â€“ Innsbruck\r\nBreakfast at your hotel, check-out. Make your own way to the train station for your onward journey to Innsbruck. On arrival at Innsbruck station, make your own way to your hotel. Check in. Later in the afternoon proceed for Swarovski crystal worldâ€™s tour.Founded by Daniel Swarovski in the Austrian village of Wittenâ€™s on the outskirts of Innsbruck. Swarovski crystal worlds invites you to discover the worldâ€™s leading manufacturer of precision-cut crystal. 800,000 hand-mounted crystals display the glittering world of Swarovski tempting you into a world of fantasy. Rest of the day at leisure. Overnight at your hotel.\r\n\r\n', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
