('753978', 6, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.Venice\r\nBreakfast at your hotel.After breakfast, proceed for Half day visit to Murano, Burano and Torcello Islands.Our first stop is Murano, where you can see the antique art of making glass and lampworking. Murano has been famous for its glassmaking since the thirteenth century when the Venetian Republic ordered all glassmakers to leave the mainland because of fear of fire. Most settled in Murano and quickly became the most prominent citizens.\r\nThe second island stop is Burano, known for its lacework and brightly colored homes. Your guide speaks English, Spanish, German and French and is happy to tell you all about the history of the area, including its visit by Leonardo da Vinci.\r\nThe third and last stop on the three and a half hour tour is Torcello, a quiet and sparsely populated island. It is considered the oldest continuously populated region of Venice and once held the largest population of the Republic of Venice. Torcello was once more powerful even than Venice itself, due to the lagoonâ€™s salt marshes that were Torcelloâ€™ s economic backbone and its close trading and cultural links with Constantinople. The island has since fallen in fortune, but relics of its bygone glory still remain, including the Cathedral of Santa Maria Assunta, founded in 639 and still containing stunning mosaics to this day.Overnight at your hotel.\r\n', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
('753978', 7, 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', '.Venice â€“ Florence\r\nBreakfast at hotel, check-out and make your own way to the train station for your onward journey to Florence.  On arrival in Florence, check into your hotel. During afternoon you can proceed for Pisa half day tourcome and discover Pisa and its famous leaning tower. Travel from Florence and lay your eyes on the beautiful renaissance piazzas and Romanesque buildings of Pisa. Discover another Tuscan treasure and take a trip to Pisa. Known worldwide for its famous leaning tower, this tour will take you beyond its iconic symbol to the equally fascinating streets, alleyways and squares that run through the city. \r\nWe depart from Florence by coach or minivan to Pisa and once we arrive an authorized city guide will accompany you to the exterior of the leaning tower and monumental cemetery. Discover the charm of the  famous Piazza dei Miracoli and visit the interior of the cathedral before having some free time to roam the renaissance piazzas and Romanesque buildings of Pisa. You have the option to join the leaning tower tour to make your way up the 296 steps of the tower without having to queue! The breathtaking views from the top will be all the more worth it, and youâ€™ll get a unique birds-eye view over Pisaâ€™s rooftops and piazzas. \r\n\r\nAs you wander the streets, youâ€™ll geta sense of what Pisa is truly known for in Italy: its education. It is home to one of the most prestigious higher learning institutions in Europe, and youâ€™ll see the many students and student hang-outs once you venture off the piazza dei miracoli. Return to Florence and overnight at your hotel.\r\n\r\n', 'NA', 'NA', 'Active'),
